        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 2:58PM CDT by NWS Austin/San Antonio TX</headline>
        <description>At 257 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Geronimo, or near New Braunfels, moving northwest at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
New Braunfels, San Marcos, Seguin, Wimberley, Canyon Lake Dam, Canyon
Lake, McQueeney, Kingsbury, Geronimo, Zorn, Hunter, Nolte, Zipp,
Sattler, Freiheit, Gruene, and New Braunfels National Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
